<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>when we create module controller with zf.bat it creates wrong class for controller. It creates only class name without prefix of the module name.</p>

<p>example:
zf.bat create controller list 1 blog</p>

<p>it creates in modules/blog/controller/ListController.php
class ListController extends Zend_Controller_Action
{</p>

<pre><code>public function init() {/* Initialize action controller here */}
public function indexAction(){ // action body}
</code></pre>

<p>}</p>

<p>but the right name would be with the prefix of module name
class Blog_ListController extends Zend_Controller_Action
{</p>

<pre><code>public function init() {/* Initialize action controller here */}
public function indexAction(){ // action body}
</code></pre>

<p>}</p>

